headline: Coca-Cola forecasts sluggish revenue growth in 2026
summary: STORY: Coca-Cola on Tuesday missed Wall Street expectations for fourth-quarter revenue.It also forecast muted growth for 2026, as demand weakened in North America and Asia.The news sent its shares down about 4% in premarket trading.The company has been raising prices for its beverages to offset higher input costs.But it comes at a time when U.S. consumers are increasingly looking for cheaper options as inflation squeezes budgets.Rival PepsiCo said last week it would cut prices on key snacks such as Lay's and Doritos.Consumers had pushed back against several rounds of price hikes over the last few years.Coca-Cola expects 2026 organic revenue to grow 4% to 5%, compared with a 5% rise last year.The company reported fourth-quarter revenue of $11.82 billion, missing estimates of just over $12 billion.

headline: Coca-Cola demand rises in fourth quarter despite higher prices but outlook sinks shares
summary: Coca-Cola saw stronger U.S. demand in the fourth quarter despite higher prices.  Unit case volumes also rose by 1% in North America, reversing several quarters of flat or declining sales.  Coke said it hiked prices 4% in North America and 1% globally during the quarter.

headline: Coca-Cola (NYSE:KO) Misses Q4 CY2025 Revenue Estimates
summary: Beverage company Coca-Cola (NYSE:KO) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025 as sales rose 3.7% year on year to $11.82 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.58 per share was 2.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Coca-Cola Reports Fourth Quarter and Full Year 2025 Results
summary: ATLANTA, February 10, 2026--The Coca-Cola Company today reported fourth quarter and full year 2025 results. "I’m encouraged by our performance in 2025 which showed both the resilience and momentum that define our business," said James Quincey, Chairman and CEO of The Coca-Cola Company. "Looking ahead, we will focus on executing our strategy even better and positioning our system for long-term success."
